A mythic and emotionally charged hero‚Äôs journey, ‚ÄúDune‚Äù tells the story of Paul Atreides, a brilliant and gifted young man born into a great destiny beyond his understanding, who must travel to the most dangerous planet  in  the  universe  to  ensure  the  future  of  his  family  and  his  people. description: Why do ships and planes vanish without a trace in the Bermuda Triangle? If you draw up a map, trace a line connecting the island of Bermuda, Puerto Rico, Miami, and back to Bermuda, what do you get?  Yes, it‚Äôs a triangle ‚Äì a sinister polygon known for mysteriously swallowing over 2,000 ships and 200 aircraft over centuries! And here's a story about the Bermuda Triangle you probably didn‚Äôt hear about. So, the airplane involved was a Beechcraft Bonanza single-engine aircraft. Onboard, pilot Bruce Gernon had two passengers: his father and business partner. They took off from Andros Island in the Bahamas and headed northwest for the Florida coast. It was December 4, 1970. This was a typical flight Bruce had made dozens of times before! But this time would be different. They would face really unexplainable and maybe even mysterious things‚Ä¶#brightsidePreview photo credit: Lancaster, USA - March 24, 2018, Beechcraft F33C Bonanza on display during Los Angeles County Air Show at William J. description: Hello friends! Apologies for the long absence, but we are trying to get things back on track. No, this video didn‚Äôt take us 3 months to make - we filmed a bunch of videos in July and this is the first of them to be released! It‚Äôs not a magnum opus, just supposed to be fun and lighthearted. If you want to read more about our plans, you can check out my blog post here:https://www.safiyasnewintrosong.com/single-post/2020/09/04/where-have-we-beenNow, onto the video! A few weeks ago, somewhere deep in a visual ASMR YouTube rabbit hole, I discovered the online acrylic pour art community - where people essentially make interesting color combos of paint in a cup, then pour that cup onto a canvas or object - and then manipulate that object to create truly mesmerizing, rainbow, psychedelic pieces of art. And I was instantly hooked - just something about the way the paints flow from the cup and then slide around the canvas really got me, ya know? So I decided to pick an acrylic pour art video and try to follow it myself, to see if I could do it too. So I chose a pouring guru, Tiktus color art, and got to work.What do you guys think of my ~acrylic pouring adventure~?This video is NOT sponsored!!Safiya's Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/safiyany/Twitter: https://twitter.com/safiyajnFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/safnygaard/The tutorial we followed is here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yndPwAMGEggYou can check out Tiktus‚Äôs channel here: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCeAvBShy5a2_vTFflQG_zWgMUSICVia AudioNetwork

description: This Video Is Dedicated To Their Love Story. Wakanda ForeverSubscribe: http://bit.ly/Subscribe-to-Talko-------------------------------------------------------------------------The tragic passing of the beloved actor, Chadwick Boseman has affected everyone. We will remember his role as King T‚ÄôChalla in Marvel‚Äôs Black Panther. We will also remember him as an inspirational person. He was very vocal about his passions. During his last moments, he spent his time at home, with his family and his wife. Unbeknownst to the world, Chadwick had married his finance, Taylor Simone Ledward after a long-lasting relationship. They were both very private people but showed their love for each other publicly. We will never forget the moment Chadwick declared his love for his future wife at the NAACP Awards. We will also never forget the beautiful photos of them smiling on red carpets and sitting courtside at basketball games. Many of their precious moments happened in California, the state is where Simone was born and raised. The couple spent much of their time in Los Angeles, California but Chadwick had also spent time in the U.K, Washington, and Brooklyn. When he settled down in California to pursue his acting career, he found his love, Simone. He started off with biopics of prominent figures and reached superstardom with his role as King T‚ÄôChalla in Black Panther, with Simone always by his side. Behind all the flashing lights, there was his private life. He had a very loving relationship with Simone. She was with him in his final moments. How will you remember Chadwick Boseman? title: The risks posed by Vettel's Aston Martin F1 deal
tags: formula 1|f1|formula one|Sebastian Vettel|Racing Point|Aston Martin|F1 2021|Lance Stroll|Sergio Perez|Lawrence Stroll|Stroll F1|F1 driver market|F1 silly season|F1 news|Ferrari|F1 latest|F1 updates|Scott Mitchell|The Race|The-race.com|@wearetherace
description: Sebastian Vettel to Aston Martin in Formula 1 (aka Racing Point) is a done deal. For 2021 he replaces Sergio Perez, and will slot in alongside Lance Stroll. It's a marquee signing for the team's Aston rebrand next year, and gives it a world champion driver at a time when it wants to take the next step up to becoming a race-winning team. But is success for this partnership a slam dunk? In this video, Scott Mitchell looks at the risks on both sides, as Vettel hopes the team can build some real upward momentum, Racing Point banks on getting the fired-up version of Vettel, and we take a moment to spare a thought for Perez for being left on the sidelines by a team he has played a pivotal role with for many years.READ MORE HERE: - Our verdict on Vettel's move: https://the-race.com/formula-1/our-verdict-on-vettels-aston-martin-f1-move/- Why Perez should leave F1: https://the-race.com/formula-1/sergio-perez-should-leave-f1-after-aston-martin-snub/Subscribe: http://the-race.com/youtube_subscribeWebsite: http://the-race.com/Twitter: http://twitter.com/WeAreTheRaceInstagram: http://instagram.com/WeAreTheRaceFacebook: http://facebook.com/WeAreTheRacePodcasts: http://the-race.com/podcastsThanks for watching - please like, share and comment, please also hit subscribe to show your support so we'll keep doing what we're doing.#Formula1 #Vettel #AstonMartinhttps://www.the-race.comhttp://www.twitter.com/wearetherace

A super big thanks to David Linderman, Jeremy Fielding, Trent, and David Woodall (the welder).I realize most people who support Smarter Every Day don't do it for transactional reasons, (ie, I'll support Smarter Every Day to get stuff).  I also realized that there is often a mental hurdle that must be crossed before support on Patreon starts.  My thought is that I'd really like to give folks a baseball, and it might provide enough momentum to get over that initial hurdle.  I signed the first shipment of baseballs I received, but I only have so many of those.  There's no implication that my signature is worth anything.... it's just kind of what you do with baseballs... it's a tradition.  After a certain number, it will transition to unsigned baseballs.  I've got enough signed baseballs to over all existing Patrons, and many more, but I will wait a month or so to see how many I need to get, then I'll order the second batch.  I like to support jobs and pay people for what they're good at.  The machinists and welders who made the parts in this video for example. title: Leopard Walks Amongst People in Restaurant
tags: Kruger|national|park|Animals|animal|Wildlife|Kruger national park|eating|Battle|south africa|Kruger Park|Africa|hunt|attack|kill|safari|Game Reserve|nature|chase|territory|watch latest sightings animatedcams videos|leopard walks among people|leopard enters lodge|leopard enters restaurant|leopard stalking people|leopard in same room as people|leopard seen from room|leopard in lodge|leopard in camp|leopard in tent
description: When you go to a restaurant in Hollywood, you might bump into a celebrity or two. But - when you go to a restaurant in South Africa, you might bump into a leopard or two‚Ä¶BOOK YOUR TRIP TO KRUGER: http://bit.ly/BookatKruger Watch this incredibly close moment caught on camera of a leopard that entered a lodge‚Äôs restaurant full of guests trying to hunt a bushbuck.Send in your wildlife video here, and earn money: https://www.latestsightings.com/partnership This sighting was filmed at Singita Ebony Lodge a few days ago by 39-year old, Innovation Edge philanthropy fund' global partnerships lead, Erika Wiese, and her friend Marie-Louise Kruger. We‚Äôd also like to thank Erika for pledging all proceeds from this video towards leopard conservation through the Singita Lowveld Conservation Trust.Erika Wiese tells us the story of how this sighting played out:‚ÄúMyself, my uncle and two of my closest friends continued chatting on the deck after breakfast. The rest of the family had gone to their rooms to rest before the afternoon game drive. Vervet monkeys are one of the best ways to know there is a predator around, by listening to their alarm calls. This particular morning, vervet monkeys alerted us to the presence of a leopard that made its way onto the upper deck, crossed the lower deck and then made its way from the lodge to remain undetected.‚Äù‚ÄúThe leopard was seen stalking a bushbuck in the riverbed in front of the lodge earlier. Singita's staff is well-trained to deal with encounters of this kind and have strict safety protocols in place to ensure the safety of both staff and guests in these situations, we were, therefore, able to remain calm, silent and in awe of the beautiful creature that was so close to us.‚Äù‚ÄúWe felt complete awe, reverence, respect and gratitude. What a rare experience to have such an encounter with a leopard. The situation proved that wildlife and people can live and interact with each other in harmony and respect.‚Äù It was as if the leopard knew that for this instance, it was in the human‚Äôs territory.‚ÄúThe sighting ended with the leopard strolling calmly away from the deck area and out of sight towards the bushbuck who you can hear alarm calling at the end.‚Äù‚ÄúThis was extremely rare for me and all I can say to someone in that situation is to stay calm and respectful.‚ÄùCredits: Erika Wiese, Marie-Louise Kruger, Singita Ebony Lodge and Roar AfricaTo license the footage: Contact@LatestSightings.comGet some of our exclusive specials at the Kruger National Park (Free nights): https://www.latestsightings.com/specialsSnapchat: LatestSightingsTwitter & Instagram: @LatestKrugerFor live wildlife sightings in the Kruger National Park: http://www.latestsightings.com/And like our Facebook page for great sightings and photos: https://www.facebook.com/latestsightingskrugerSubscribe to us on YouTube: http://www.youtube.com/LatestSightings

title: Drag Racing the WORLD'S MOST EXPENSIVE CARS! Bugatti vs Koenigsegg vs Pagani
tags: Hypercar|Drag|Races|Racing|Launch Control|Bugatti|Koenigsegg|Pagani|Ferrari|Lamborghini|Head to head|Versus|Vs|Race|Flat Out|Chiron|Regera|Huayra|Zonda|One:1|Agera R|LaFerrari|Veyron|Supercar Owners Circle|Gstaad|Runway|Drag Strip|Switzerland|Ultimate|Showdown|Shmee|Shmee150
description: The world's most expensive cars are rarely up against one another on a drag strip, but here's a feast for the eyes! From the Bugatti Chiron versus the Lamborghini Aventador SVJ, and the Koenigsegg One:1 against the Pagani Zonda Cinque, to putting my own McLaren Senna and Mercedes SLS AMG Black Series against one another; it's all here on the runway at Gstaad Airport as part of the Supercar Owners Circle weekend!The Supercar Owners Circle weekend in Gstaad, Switzerland sees the most exclusive and rare cars in the world in attendance, with towards 100 hypercars featuring just about every model of Bugatti, Koenigsegg, Pagani and more. Going flat out we have everything from the Chiron to LaFerrari, and One:1 to Zonda Cinque, mixed in with the Carrera GT, GFG Style 2030, Veyron Vitesse, and of course the likes of the Regera flat out. Obviously the loudest of the bunch is the Lamborghini Aventador SVJ, trying its luck against a Bugatti Chiron!In attendance at SOC with two of the Shmeemobiles, the McLaren Senna and Mercedes SLS AMG Black Series, it is of course a must that we put the two up against one another to show the difference between a 'fast car' and a 'really fast car'. Giving the SLS BS a small head start, being piloted by @benzeneben, the 800hp of the Senna ultimately causes an obliteration as it flies by on the way to 270km/h (168mph). It must be said though, that the SLS sounds the absolute part thanks to the RENNtech R1 modifications.We're treated to some great races on the Gstaad Airport runway:Bugatti Veyron Vitesse vs Porsche Carrera GTBugatti Veyron Grand Sport vs Porsche 918 SpyderFerrari LaFerrari vs GFG Style 2030Koenigsegg Agera R vs Pagani Zonda Cinque (manual)Koenigsegg Regera vs Koenigsegg One:1Pagani Huayra Roadster vs Koenigsegg RegeraFerrari 599 GTZ Zagato Nibbio Coupe vs SpyderLamborghini Aventador SVJ Roadster vs Mercedes SLS AMG Black SeriesFerrari Enzo vs McLaren SennaMcLaren Senna vs Ferrari F12tdfLamborghini Aventador SVJ Roadster vs Bugatti Chiron SportPorsche Carrera GT vs Pagani Zonda FPagani Huayra BC vs Pagani Huayra RoadsterMercedes SLR McLaren Roadster vs Aston Martin DBS Superleggera VolanteAudi R8 Spyder vs HK Engineering 300SLFerrari LaFerrari vs Ferrari 488 Pista SpiderBugatti Chiron Sport vs Mercedes SLR McLaren 722SAston Martin Vanquish Zagato vs Bugatti Veyron Super SportBugatti Veyron Vitesse vs Bugatti Veyron Grand SportPagani Zonda 760 Unica vs Porsche Carrera GTFerrari LaFerrari vs Ferrari EnzoKoenigsegg One:1 vs Pagani Zonda CinqueMcLaren Senna vs Mercedes SLS AMG Black SeriesDrag racing is no easy task, especially with just one go in a high pressure environment. This is not a competitive and fully prepared head to head, but rather some fun during the SOC weekend. In many cases the drivers are learning their cars or doing a launch for the first time, these are privately owned vehicles to the most part and it's absolutely fantastic to see so many owners being happy to use their vehicles and for them to be shared with the audience!Thanks for watching, TimSubscribe: http://bit.ly/Shmee150YTWebsite: http://www.shmee150.comShop: http://shop.shmee150.comInstagram: http://www.instagram.com/shmee150Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/shmee150

description: Our perception of time is incredibly malleable ‚Äî no wonder the pandemic upended it.Subscribe to our channel! http://goo.gl/0bsAjOThere used to be this thing called a party. The concept was simple ‚Äî gather a bunch of living, breathing bodies in the same place at the same time and just see what happens. And if my friends wanted me to be on time to a party, they‚Äôd lie.I wasn‚Äôt proud of my reputation with time. Once, someone was describing their color blindness to me and it reminded me a lot of how I feel about time. How I know that 3 pm and 3:05 pm are technically different, but I personally don‚Äôt perceive that contrast.I tried my best to banish those thoughts. I bought clocks and set them to five minutes early. And I was finally closing the gap ‚Äî becoming one of those people who holds the reins of time. And then ‚Äî the pandemic happened.And suddenly Tuesdays were Thursdays were Sundays. The whole world joined me in temporal disorientation ‚Äî even my punctual superiors were at a loss. They knew how to arrive five minutes early ‚Äî not how to repeat the same five minutes 43,854 times.Maybe we‚Äôve all been too fixated on keeping track of time when what we need most is vocabulary to describe the new colors of time.We were thrilled to work with filmmaker Sindha Agha on this video.
